14const char* getTypeName( int type )
15{
16 static const char* type_names[] = { "8u", "8s", "16u", "16s", "32s", "32f", "64f", "ptr" };
17 return type_names[CV_MAT_DEPTH(type)];
18}

20int typeByName( const char* name )
21{
22 int i;
23 for( i = 0; i < CV_DEPTH_MAX; i++ )
24 if( strcmp(name, getTypeName(i)) == 0 )
25 return i;
26 return -1;
27}

29string vec2str( const string& sep, const int* v, size_t nelems )
30{
31 char buf[32];
32 string result = "";
33 for( size_t i = 0; i < nelems; i++ )
34 {
35 sprintf(buf, "%d", v[i]);
36 result += string(buf);
37 if( i < nelems - 1 )
38 result += sep;
39 }
40 return result;
41}

44Size randomSize(RNG& rng, double maxSizeLog)
45{
46 double width_log = rng.uniform(0., maxSizeLog);
47 double height_log = rng.uniform(0., maxSizeLog - width_log);
48 if( (unsigned)rng % 2 != 0 )
49 std::swap(width_log, height_log);
50 Size sz;
51 sz.width = cvRound(exp(width_log));
52 sz.height = cvRound(exp(height_log));
53 return sz;
54}
55
56void randomSize(RNG& rng, int minDims, int maxDims, double maxSizeLog, vector<int>& sz)
57{
58 int i, dims = rng.uniform(minDims, maxDims+1);
59 sz.resize(dims);
60 for( i = 0; i < dims; i++ )
61 {
62 double v = rng.uniform(0., maxSizeLog);
63 maxSizeLog -= v;
64 sz[i] = cvRound(exp(v));
65 }
66 for( i = 0; i < dims; i++ )
67 {
68 int j = rng.uniform(0, dims);
69 int k = rng.uniform(0, dims);
70 std::swap(sz[j], sz[k]);
71 }
72}
73
74int randomType(RNG& rng, int typeMask, int minChannels, int maxChannels)
75{
76 int channels = rng.uniform(minChannels, maxChannels+1);
77 int depth = 0;
78 CV_Assert((typeMask & DEPTH_MASK_ALL) != 0);
79 for(;;)
80 {
81 depth = rng.uniform(CV_8U, CV_64F+1);
82 if( ((1 << depth) & typeMask) != 0 )
83 break;
84 }
85 return CV_MAKETYPE(depth, channels);
86}
87
88double getMinVal(int depth)
89{
90 depth = CV_MAT_DEPTH(depth);
91 double val = depth == CV_8U ? 0 : depth == CV_8S ? SCHAR_MIN : depth == CV_16U ? 0 :
92 depth == CV_16S ? SHRT_MIN : depth == CV_32S ? INT_MIN :
93 depth == CV_32F ? -FLT_MAX : depth == CV_64F ? -DBL_MAX : -1;
94 CV_Assert(val != -1);
95 return val;
96}
97
98double getMaxVal(int depth)
99{
100 depth = CV_MAT_DEPTH(depth);
101 double val = depth == CV_8U ? UCHAR_MAX : depth == CV_8S ? SCHAR_MAX : depth == CV_16U ? USHRT_MAX :
102 depth == CV_16S ? SHRT_MAX : depth == CV_32S ? INT_MAX :
103 depth == CV_32F ? FLT_MAX : depth == CV_64F ? DBL_MAX : -1;
104 CV_Assert(val != -1);
105 return val;
106}

108Mat randomMat(RNG& rng, Size size, int type, double minVal, double maxVal, bool useRoi)
109{
110 Size size0 = size;
111 if( useRoi )
112 {
113 size0.width += std::max(rng.uniform(0, 10) - 5, 0);
114 size0.height += std::max(rng.uniform(0, 10) - 5, 0);
115 }
116
117 Mat m(size0, type);
118
119 rng.fill(m, RNG::UNIFORM, minVal, maxVal);
120 if( size0 == size )
121 return m;
122 return m(Rect((size0.width-size.width)/2, (size0.height-size.height)/2, size.width, size.height));
123}
124
125Mat randomMat(RNG& rng, const vector<int>& size, int type, double minVal, double maxVal, bool useRoi)
126{
127 int i, dims = (int)size.size();
128 vector<int> size0(dims);
129 vector<Range> r(dims);
130 bool eqsize = true;
131 for( i = 0; i < dims; i++ )
132 {
133 size0[i] = size[i];
134 r[i] = Range::all();
135 if( useRoi )
136 {
137 size0[i] += std::max(rng.uniform(0, 5) - 2, 0);
138 r[i] = Range((size0[i] - size[i])/2, (size0[i] - size[i])/2 + size[i]);
139 }
140 eqsize = eqsize && size[i] == size0[i];
141 }
142
143 Mat m(dims, &size0[0], type);
144
145 rng.fill(m, RNG::UNIFORM, minVal, maxVal);
146 if( eqsize )
147 return m;
148 return m(&r[0]);
149}

151void add(const Mat& _a, double alpha, const Mat& _b, double beta,
152 Scalar gamma, Mat& c, int ctype, bool calcAbs)
153{
154 Mat a = _a, b = _b;
155 if( a.empty() || alpha == 0 )
156 {
157 // both alpha and beta can be 0, but at least one of a and b must be non-empty array,
158 // otherwise we do not know the size of the output (and may be type of the output, when ctype<0)
159 CV_Assert( !a.empty() || !b.empty() );
160 if( !b.empty() )
161 {
162 a = b;
163 alpha = beta;
164 b = Mat();
165 beta = 0;
166 }
167 }
168 if( b.empty() || beta == 0 )
169 {
170 b = Mat();
171 beta = 0;
172 }
173 else
174 CV_Assert(a.size == b.size);
175
176 if( ctype < 0 )
177 ctype = a.depth();
178 ctype = CV_MAKETYPE(CV_MAT_DEPTH(ctype), a.channels());
179 c.create(a.dims, &a.size[0], ctype);
180 const Mat *arrays[] = {&a, &b, &c, 0};
181 Mat planes[3], buf[3];
182
183 NAryMatIterator it(arrays, planes);
184 size_t i, nplanes = it.nplanes;
185 int cn=a.channels();
186 int total = (int)planes[0].total(), maxsize = std::min(12*12*std::max(12/cn, 1), total);
187
188 CV_Assert(planes[0].rows == 1);
189 buf[0].create(1, maxsize, CV_64FC(cn));
190 if(!b.empty())
191 buf[1].create(1, maxsize, CV_64FC(cn));
192 buf[2].create(1, maxsize, CV_64FC(cn));
193 scalarToRawData(gamma, buf[2].data, CV_64FC(cn), (int)(maxsize*cn));
194
195 for( i = 0; i < nplanes; i++, ++it)
196 {
197 for( int j = 0; j < total; j += maxsize )
198 {
199 int j2 = std::min(j + maxsize, total);
200 Mat apart0 = planes[0].colRange(j, j2);
201 Mat cpart0 = planes[2].colRange(j, j2);
202 Mat apart = buf[0].colRange(0, j2 - j);
203
204 apart0.convertTo(apart, apart.type(), alpha);
205 size_t k, n = (j2 - j)*cn;
206 double* aptr = (double*)apart.data;
207 const double* gptr = (const double*)buf[2].data;
208
209 if( b.empty() )
210 {
211 for( k = 0; k < n; k++ )
212 aptr[k] += gptr[k];
213 }
214 else
215 {
216 Mat bpart0 = planes[1].colRange((int)j, (int)j2);
217 Mat bpart = buf[1].colRange(0, (int)(j2 - j));
218 bpart0.convertTo(bpart, bpart.type(), beta);
219 const double* bptr = (const double*)bpart.data;
220
221 for( k = 0; k < n; k++ )
222 aptr[k] += bptr[k] + gptr[k];
223 }
224 if( calcAbs )
225 for( k = 0; k < n; k++ )
226 aptr[k] = fabs(aptr[k]);
227 apart.convertTo(cpart0, cpart0.type(), 1, 0);
228 }
229 }
230}

233template<typename _Tp1, typename _Tp2> inline void
234convert_(const _Tp1* src, _Tp2* dst, size_t total, double alpha, double beta)
235{
236 size_t i;
237 if( alpha == 1 && beta == 0 )
238 for( i = 0; i < total; i++ )
239 dst[i] = saturate_cast<_Tp2>(src[i]);
240 else if( beta == 0 )
241 for( i = 0; i < total; i++ )
242 dst[i] = saturate_cast<_Tp2>(src[i]*alpha);
243 else
244 for( i = 0; i < total; i++ )
245 dst[i] = saturate_cast<_Tp2>(src[i]*alpha + beta);
246}
247
248template<typename _Tp> inline void
249convertTo(const _Tp* src, void* dst, int dtype, size_t total, double alpha, double beta)
250{
251 switch( CV_MAT_DEPTH(dtype) )
252 {
253 case CV_8U:
254 convert_(src, (uchar*)dst, total, alpha, beta);
255 break;
256 case CV_8S:
257 convert_(src, (schar*)dst, total, alpha, beta);
258 break;
259 case CV_16U:
260 convert_(src, (ushort*)dst, total, alpha, beta);
261 break;
262 case CV_16S:
263 convert_(src, (short*)dst, total, alpha, beta);
264 break;
265 case CV_32S:
266 convert_(src, (int*)dst, total, alpha, beta);
267 break;
268 case CV_32F:
269 convert_(src, (float*)dst, total, alpha, beta);
270 break;
271 case CV_64F:
272 convert_(src, (double*)dst, total, alpha, beta);
273 break;
274 default:
275 CV_Assert(0);
276 }
277}
278
279void convert(const Mat& src, Mat& dst, int dtype, double alpha, double beta)
280{
281 dtype = CV_MAKETYPE(CV_MAT_DEPTH(dtype), src.channels());
282 dst.create(src.dims, &src.size[0], dtype);
283 if( alpha == 0 )
284 {
285 set( dst, Scalar::all(beta) );
286 return;
287 }
288 if( dtype == src.type() && alpha == 1 && beta == 0 )
289 {
290 copy( src, dst );
291 return;
292 }
293
294 const Mat *arrays[]={&src, &dst, 0};
295 Mat planes[2];
296
297 NAryMatIterator it(arrays, planes);
298 size_t total = planes[0].total()*planes[0].channels();
299 size_t i, nplanes = it.nplanes;
300
301 for( i = 0; i < nplanes; i++, ++it)
302 {
303 const uchar* sptr = planes[0].data;
304 uchar* dptr = planes[1].data;
305
306 switch( src.depth() )
307 {
308 case CV_8U:
309 convertTo((const uchar*)sptr, dptr, dtype, total, alpha, beta);
310 break;
311 case CV_8S:
312 convertTo((const schar*)sptr, dptr, dtype, total, alpha, beta);
313 break;
314 case CV_16U:
315 convertTo((const ushort*)sptr, dptr, dtype, total, alpha, beta);
316 break;
317 case CV_16S:
318 convertTo((const short*)sptr, dptr, dtype, total, alpha, beta);
319 break;
320 case CV_32S:
321 convertTo((const int*)sptr, dptr, dtype, total, alpha, beta);
322 break;
323 case CV_32F:
324 convertTo((const float*)sptr, dptr, dtype, total, alpha, beta);
325 break;
326 case CV_64F:
327 convertTo((const double*)sptr, dptr, dtype, total, alpha, beta);
328 break;
329 }
330 }
331}

334void copy(const Mat& src, Mat& dst, const Mat& mask, bool invertMask)
335{
336 dst.create(src.dims, &src.size[0], src.type());
337
338 if(mask.empty())
339 {
340 const Mat* arrays[] = {&src, &dst, 0};
341 Mat planes[2];
342 NAryMatIterator it(arrays, planes);
343 size_t i, nplanes = it.nplanes;
344 size_t planeSize = planes[0].total()*src.elemSize();
345
346 for( i = 0; i < nplanes; i++, ++it )
347 memcpy(planes[1].data, planes[0].data, planeSize);
348
349 return;
350 }
351
352 CV_Assert( src.size == mask.size && mask.type() == CV_8U );
353
354 const Mat *arrays[]={&src, &dst, &mask, 0};
355 Mat planes[3];
356
357 NAryMatIterator it(arrays, planes);
358 size_t j, k, elemSize = src.elemSize(), total = planes[0].total();
359 size_t i, nplanes = it.nplanes;
360
361 for( i = 0; i < nplanes; i++, ++it)
362 {
363 const uchar* sptr = planes[0].data;
364 uchar* dptr = planes[1].data;
365 const uchar* mptr = planes[2].data;
366
367 for( j = 0; j < total; j++, sptr += elemSize, dptr += elemSize )
368 {
369 if( (mptr[j] != 0) ^ invertMask )
370 for( k = 0; k < elemSize; k++ )
371 dptr[k] = sptr[k];
372 }
373 }
374}

377void set(Mat& dst, const Scalar& gamma, const Mat& mask)
378{
379 double buf[12];
380 scalarToRawData(gamma, &buf, dst.type(), dst.channels());
381 const uchar* gptr = (const uchar*)&buf[0];
382
383 if(mask.empty())
384 {
385 const Mat* arrays[] = {&dst, 0};
386 Mat plane;
387 NAryMatIterator it(arrays, &plane);
388 size_t i, nplanes = it.nplanes;
389 size_t j, k, elemSize = dst.elemSize(), planeSize = plane.total()*elemSize;
390
391 for( k = 1; k < elemSize; k++ )
392 if( gptr[k] != gptr[0] )
393 break;
394 bool uniform = k >= elemSize;
395
396 for( i = 0; i < nplanes; i++, ++it )
397 {
398 uchar* dptr = plane.data;
399 if( uniform )
400 memset( dptr, gptr[0], planeSize );
401 else if( i == 0 )
402 {
403 for( j = 0; j < planeSize; j += elemSize, dptr += elemSize )
404 for( k = 0; k < elemSize; k++ )
405 dptr[k] = gptr[k];
406 }
407 else
408 memcpy(dptr, dst.data, planeSize);
409 }
410 return;
411 }
412
413 CV_Assert( dst.size == mask.size && mask.type() == CV_8U );
414
415 const Mat *arrays[]={&dst, &mask, 0};
416 Mat planes[2];
417
418 NAryMatIterator it(arrays, planes);
419 size_t j, k, elemSize = dst.elemSize(), total = planes[0].total();
420 size_t i, nplanes = it.nplanes;
421
422 for( i = 0; i < nplanes; i++, ++it)
423 {
424 uchar* dptr = planes[0].data;
425 const uchar* mptr = planes[1].data;
426
427 for( j = 0; j < total; j++, dptr += elemSize )
428 {
429 if( mptr[j] )
430 for( k = 0; k < elemSize; k++ )
431 dptr[k] = gptr[k];
432 }
433 }
434}

437void insert(const Mat& src, Mat& dst, int coi)
438{
439 CV_Assert( dst.size == src.size && src.depth() == dst.depth() &&
440 0 <= coi && coi < dst.channels() );
441
442 const Mat* arrays[] = {&src, &dst, 0};
443 Mat planes[2];
444 NAryMatIterator it(arrays, planes);
445 size_t i, nplanes = it.nplanes;
446 size_t j, k, size0 = src.elemSize(), size1 = dst.elemSize(), total = planes[0].total();
447
448 for( i = 0; i < nplanes; i++, ++it )
449 {
450 const uchar* sptr = planes[0].data;
451 uchar* dptr = planes[1].data + coi*size0;
452
453 for( j = 0; j < total; j++, sptr += size0, dptr += size1 )
454 {
455 for( k = 0; k < size0; k++ )
456 dptr[k] = sptr[k];
457 }
458 }

487void transpose(const Mat& src, Mat& dst)
488{
489 CV_Assert(src.dims == 2);
490 dst.create(src.cols, src.rows, src.type());
491 int i, j, k, esz = (int)src.elemSize();
492
493 for( i = 0; i < dst.rows; i++ )
494 {
495 const uchar* sptr = src.ptr(0) + i*esz;
496 uchar* dptr = dst.ptr(i);
497
498 for( j = 0; j < dst.cols; j++, sptr += src.step[0], dptr += esz )
499 {
500 for( k = 0; k < esz; k++ )
501 dptr[k] = sptr[k];
502 }
503 }
504}

507template<typename _Tp> static void
508randUniInt_(RNG& rng, _Tp* data, size_t total, int cn, const Scalar& scale, const Scalar& delta)
509{
510 for( size_t i = 0; i < total; i += cn )
511 for( int k = 0; k < cn; k++ )
512 {
513 int val = cvFloor( randInt(rng)*scale[k] + delta[k] );
514 data[i + k] = saturate_cast<_Tp>(val);
515 }
516}
517
518
519template<typename _Tp> static void
520randUniFlt_(RNG& rng, _Tp* data, size_t total, int cn, const Scalar& scale, const Scalar& delta)
521{
522 for( size_t i = 0; i < total; i += cn )
523 for( int k = 0; k < cn; k++ )
524 {
525 double val = randReal(rng)*scale[k] + delta[k];
526 data[i + k] = saturate_cast<_Tp>(val);
527 }
528}

530
531void randUni( RNG& rng, Mat& a, const Scalar& param0, const Scalar& param1 )
532{
533 Scalar scale = param0;
534 Scalar delta = param1;
535 double C = a.depth() < CV_32F ? 1./(65536.*65536.) : 1.;
536
537 for( int k = 0; k < 4; k++ )
538 {
539 double s = scale.val[k] - delta.val[k];
540 if( s >= 0 )
541 scale.val[k] = s;
542 else
543 {
544 delta.val[k] = scale.val[k];
545 scale.val[k] = -s;
546 }
547 scale.val[k] *= C;
548 }
549
550 const Mat *arrays[]={&a, 0};
551 Mat plane;
552
553 NAryMatIterator it(arrays, &plane);
554 size_t i, nplanes = it.nplanes;
555 int depth = a.depth(), cn = a.channels();
556 size_t total = plane.total()*cn;
557
558 for( i = 0; i < nplanes; i++, ++it )
559 {
560 switch( depth )
561 {
562 case CV_8U:
563 randUniInt_(rng, plane.ptr<uchar>(), total, cn, scale, delta);
564 break;
565 case CV_8S:
566 randUniInt_(rng, plane.ptr<schar>(), total, cn, scale, delta);
567 break;
568 case CV_16U:
569 randUniInt_(rng, plane.ptr<ushort>(), total, cn, scale, delta);
570 break;
571 case CV_16S:
572 randUniInt_(rng, plane.ptr<short>(), total, cn, scale, delta);
573 break;
574 case CV_32S:
575 randUniInt_(rng, plane.ptr<int>(), total, cn, scale, delta);
576 break;
577 case CV_32F:
578 randUniFlt_(rng, plane.ptr<float>(), total, cn, scale, delta);
579 break;
580 case CV_64F:
581 randUniFlt_(rng, plane.ptr<double>(), total, cn, scale, delta);
582 break;
583 default:
584 CV_Assert(0);
585 }
586 }
587}

590template<typename _Tp> static void
591erode_(const Mat& src, Mat& dst, const vector<int>& ofsvec)
592{
593 int width = dst.cols*src.channels(), n = (int)ofsvec.size();
594 const int* ofs = &ofsvec[0];
595
596 for( int y = 0; y < dst.rows; y++ )
597 {
598 const _Tp* sptr = src.ptr<_Tp>(y);
599 _Tp* dptr = dst.ptr<_Tp>(y);
600
601 for( int x = 0; x < width; x++ )
602 {
603 _Tp result = sptr[x + ofs[0]];
604 for( int i = 1; i < n; i++ )
605 result = std::min(result, sptr[x + ofs[i]]);
606 dptr[x] = result;
607 }
608 }
609}

612template<typename _Tp> static void
613dilate_(const Mat& src, Mat& dst, const vector<int>& ofsvec)
614{
615 int width = dst.cols*src.channels(), n = (int)ofsvec.size();
616 const int* ofs = &ofsvec[0];
617
618 for( int y = 0; y < dst.rows; y++ )
619 {
620 const _Tp* sptr = src.ptr<_Tp>(y);
621 _Tp* dptr = dst.ptr<_Tp>(y);
622
623 for( int x = 0; x < width; x++ )
624 {
625 _Tp result = sptr[x + ofs[0]];
626 for( int i = 1; i < n; i++ )
627 result = std::max(result, sptr[x + ofs[i]]);
628 dptr[x] = result;
629 }
630 }
631}

633
634void erode(const Mat& _src, Mat& dst, const Mat& _kernel, Point anchor,
635 int borderType, const Scalar& _borderValue)
636{
637 //if( _src.type() == CV_16UC3 && _src.size() == Size(1, 2) )
638 // putchar('*');
639 Mat kernel = _kernel, src;
640 Scalar borderValue = _borderValue;
641 if( kernel.empty() )
642 kernel = Mat::ones(3, 3, CV_8U);
643 else
644 {
645 CV_Assert( kernel.type() == CV_8U );
646 }
647 if( anchor == Point(-1,-1) )
648 anchor = Point(kernel.cols/2, kernel.rows/2);
649 if( borderType == IPL_BORDER_CONSTANT )
650 borderValue = getMaxVal(src.depth());
651 copyMakeBorder(_src, src, anchor.y, kernel.rows - anchor.y - 1,
652 anchor.x, kernel.cols - anchor.x - 1,
653 borderType, borderValue);
654 dst.create( _src.size(), src.type() );
655
656 vector<int> ofs;
657 int step = (int)(src.step/src.elemSize1()), cn = src.channels();
658 for( int i = 0; i < kernel.rows; i++ )
659 for( int j = 0; j < kernel.cols; j++ )
660 if( kernel.at<uchar>(i, j) != 0 )
661 ofs.push_back(i*step + j*cn);
662 if( ofs.empty() )
663 ofs.push_back(anchor.y*step + anchor.x*cn);
664
665 switch( src.depth() )
666 {
667 case CV_8U:
668 erode_<uchar>(src, dst, ofs);
669 break;
670 case CV_8S:
671 erode_<schar>(src, dst, ofs);
672 break;
673 case CV_16U:
674 erode_<ushort>(src, dst, ofs);
675 break;
676 case CV_16S:
677 erode_<short>(src, dst, ofs);
678 break;
679 case CV_32S:
680 erode_<int>(src, dst, ofs);
681 break;
682 case CV_32F:
683 erode_<float>(src, dst, ofs);
684 break;
685 case CV_64F:
686 erode_<double>(src, dst, ofs);
687 break;
688 default:
689 CV_Assert(0);
690 }
691}

693void dilate(const Mat& _src, Mat& dst, const Mat& _kernel, Point anchor,
694 int borderType, const Scalar& _borderValue)
695{
696 Mat kernel = _kernel, src;
697 Scalar borderValue = _borderValue;
698 if( kernel.empty() )
699 kernel = Mat::ones(3, 3, CV_8U);
700 else
701 {
702 CV_Assert( kernel.type() == CV_8U );
703 }
704 if( anchor == Point(-1,-1) )
705 anchor = Point(kernel.cols/2, kernel.rows/2);
706 if( borderType == IPL_BORDER_CONSTANT )
707 borderValue = getMinVal(src.depth());
708 copyMakeBorder(_src, src, anchor.y, kernel.rows - anchor.y - 1,
709 anchor.x, kernel.cols - anchor.x - 1,
710 borderType, borderValue);
711 dst.create( _src.size(), src.type() );
712
713 vector<int> ofs;
714 int step = (int)(src.step/src.elemSize1()), cn = src.channels();
715 for( int i = 0; i < kernel.rows; i++ )
716 for( int j = 0; j < kernel.cols; j++ )
717 if( kernel.at<uchar>(i, j) != 0 )
718 ofs.push_back(i*step + j*cn);
719 if( ofs.empty() )
720 ofs.push_back(anchor.y*step + anchor.x*cn);
721
722 switch( src.depth() )
723 {
724 case CV_8U:
725 dilate_<uchar>(src, dst, ofs);
726 break;
727 case CV_8S:
728 dilate_<schar>(src, dst, ofs);
729 break;
730 case CV_16U:
731 dilate_<ushort>(src, dst, ofs);
732 break;
733 case CV_16S:
734 dilate_<short>(src, dst, ofs);
735 break;
736 case CV_32S:
737 dilate_<int>(src, dst, ofs);
738 break;
739 case CV_32F:
740 dilate_<float>(src, dst, ofs);
741 break;
742 case CV_64F:
743 dilate_<double>(src, dst, ofs);
744 break;
745 default:
746 CV_Assert(0);
747 }
748}

751template<typename _Tp> static void
752filter2D_(const Mat& src, Mat& dst, const vector<int>& ofsvec, const vector<double>& coeffvec)
753{
754 const int* ofs = &ofsvec[0];
755 const double* coeff = &coeffvec[0];
756 int width = dst.cols*dst.channels(), ncoeffs = (int)ofsvec.size();
757
758 for( int y = 0; y < dst.rows; y++ )
759 {
760 const _Tp* sptr = src.ptr<_Tp>(y);
761 double* dptr = dst.ptr<double>(y);
762
763 for( int x = 0; x < width; x++ )
764 {
765 double s = 0;
766 for( int i = 0; i < ncoeffs; i++ )
767 s += sptr[x + ofs[i]]*coeff[i];
768 dptr[x] = s;
769 }
770 }
771}

773
774void filter2D(const Mat& _src, Mat& dst, int ddepth, const Mat& kernel,
775 Point anchor, double delta, int borderType, const Scalar& _borderValue)
776{
777 Mat src, _dst;
778 Scalar borderValue = _borderValue;
779 CV_Assert( kernel.type() == CV_32F || kernel.type() == CV_64F );
780 if( anchor == Point(-1,-1) )
781 anchor = Point(kernel.cols/2, kernel.rows/2);
782 if( borderType == IPL_BORDER_CONSTANT )
783 borderValue = getMinVal(src.depth());
784 copyMakeBorder(_src, src, anchor.y, kernel.rows - anchor.y - 1,
785 anchor.x, kernel.cols - anchor.x - 1,
786 borderType, borderValue);
787 _dst.create( _src.size(), CV_MAKETYPE(CV_64F, src.channels()) );
788
789 vector<int> ofs;
790 vector<double> coeff(kernel.rows*kernel.cols);
791 Mat cmat(kernel.rows, kernel.cols, CV_64F, &coeff[0]);
792 convert(kernel, cmat, cmat.type());
793
794 int step = (int)(src.step/src.elemSize1()), cn = src.channels();
795 for( int i = 0; i < kernel.rows; i++ )
796 for( int j = 0; j < kernel.cols; j++ )
797 ofs.push_back(i*step + j*cn);
798
799 switch( src.depth() )
800 {
801 case CV_8U:
802 filter2D_<uchar>(src, _dst, ofs, coeff);
803 break;
804 case CV_8S:
805 filter2D_<schar>(src, _dst, ofs, coeff);
806 break;
807 case CV_16U:
808 filter2D_<ushort>(src, _dst, ofs, coeff);
809 break;
810 case CV_16S:
811 filter2D_<short>(src, _dst, ofs, coeff);
812 break;
813 case CV_32S:
814 filter2D_<int>(src, _dst, ofs, coeff);
815 break;
816 case CV_32F:
817 filter2D_<float>(src, _dst, ofs, coeff);
818 break;
819 case CV_64F:
820 filter2D_<double>(src, _dst, ofs, coeff);
821 break;
822 default:
823 CV_Assert(0);
824 }
825
826 convert(_dst, dst, ddepth, 1, delta);
827}

829
830static int borderInterpolate( int p, int len, int borderType )
831{
832 if( (unsigned)p < (unsigned)len )
833 ;
834 else if( borderType == IPL_BORDER_REPLICATE )
835 p = p < 0 ? 0 : len - 1;
836 else if( borderType == IPL_BORDER_REFLECT || borderType == IPL_BORDER_REFLECT_101 )
837 {
838 int delta = borderType == IPL_BORDER_REFLECT_101;
839 if( len == 1 )
840 return 0;
841 do
842 {
843 if( p < 0 )
844 p = -p - 1 + delta;
845 else
846 p = len - 1 - (p - len) - delta;
847 }
848 while( (unsigned)p >= (unsigned)len );
849 }
850 else if( borderType == IPL_BORDER_WRAP )
851 {
852 if( p < 0 )
853 p -= ((p-len+1)/len)*len;
854 if( p >= len )
855 p %= len;
856 }
857 else if( borderType == IPL_BORDER_CONSTANT )
858 p = -1;
859 else
860 CV_Error( CV_StsBadArg, "Unknown/unsupported border type" );
861 return p;
862}
863
864
865void copyMakeBorder(const Mat& src, Mat& dst, int top, int bottom, int left, int right,
866 int borderType, const Scalar& borderValue)
867{
868 dst.create(src.rows + top + bottom, src.cols + left + right, src.type());
869 int i, j, k, esz = (int)src.elemSize();
870 int width = src.cols*esz, width1 = dst.cols*esz;
871
872 if( borderType == IPL_BORDER_CONSTANT )
873 {
874 vector<uchar> valvec((src.cols + left + right)*esz);
875 uchar* val = &valvec[0];
876 scalarToRawData(borderValue, val, src.type(), (src.cols + left + right)*src.channels());
877
878 left *= esz;
879 right *= esz;
880 for( i = 0; i < src.rows; i++ )
881 {
882 const uchar* sptr = src.ptr(i);
883 uchar* dptr = dst.ptr(i + top) + left;
884 for( j = 0; j < left; j++ )
885 dptr[j - left] = val[j];
886 if( dptr != sptr )
887 for( j = 0; j < width; j++ )
888 dptr[j] = sptr[j];
889 for( j = 0; j < right; j++ )
890 dptr[j + width] = val[j];
891 }
892
893 for( i = 0; i < top; i++ )
894 {
895 uchar* dptr = dst.ptr(i);
896 for( j = 0; j < width1; j++ )
897 dptr[j] = val[j];
898 }
899
900 for( i = 0; i < bottom; i++ )
901 {
902 uchar* dptr = dst.ptr(i + top + src.rows);
903 for( j = 0; j < width1; j++ )
904 dptr[j] = val[j];
905 }
906 }
907 else
908 {
909 vector<int> tabvec((left + right)*esz + 1);
910 int* ltab = &tabvec[0];
911 int* rtab = &tabvec[left*esz];
912 for( i = 0; i < left; i++ )
913 {
914 j = borderInterpolate(i - left, src.cols, borderType)*esz;
915 for( k = 0; k < esz; k++ )
916 ltab[i*esz + k] = j + k;
917 }
918 for( i = 0; i < right; i++ )
919 {
920 j = borderInterpolate(src.cols + i, src.cols, borderType)*esz;
921 for( k = 0; k < esz; k++ )
922 rtab[i*esz + k] = j + k;
923 }
924
925 left *= esz;
926 right *= esz;
927 for( i = 0; i < src.rows; i++ )
928 {
929 const uchar* sptr = src.ptr(i);
930 uchar* dptr = dst.ptr(i + top);
931
932 for( j = 0; j < left; j++ )
933 dptr[j] = sptr[ltab[j]];
934 if( dptr + left != sptr )
935 {
936 for( j = 0; j < width; j++ )
937 dptr[j + left] = sptr[j];
938 }
939 for( j = 0; j < right; j++ )
940 dptr[j + left + width] = sptr[rtab[j]];
941 }
942
943 for( i = 0; i < top; i++ )
944 {
945 j = borderInterpolate(i - top, src.rows, borderType);
946 const uchar* sptr = dst.ptr(j + top);
947 uchar* dptr = dst.ptr(i);
948
949 for( k = 0; k < width1; k++ )
950 dptr[k] = sptr[k];
951 }
952
953 for( i = 0; i < bottom; i++ )
954 {
955 j = borderInterpolate(i + src.rows, src.rows, borderType);
956 const uchar* sptr = dst.ptr(j + top);
957 uchar* dptr = dst.ptr(i + top + src.rows);
958
959 for( k = 0; k < width1; k++ )
960 dptr[k] = sptr[k];
961 }
962 }
963}

966template<typename _Tp> static void
967minMaxLoc_(const _Tp* src, size_t total, size_t startidx,
968 double* _minval, double* _maxval,
969 size_t* _minpos, size_t* _maxpos,
970 const uchar* mask)
971{
972 _Tp maxval = saturate_cast<_Tp>(*_maxval), minval = saturate_cast<_Tp>(*_minval);
973 size_t minpos = *_minpos, maxpos = *_maxpos;
974
975 if( !mask )
976 {
977 for( size_t i = 0; i < total; i++ )
978 {
979 _Tp val = src[i];
980 if( minval > val || !minpos )
981 {
982 minval = val;
983 minpos = startidx + i;
984 }
985 if( maxval < val || !maxpos )
986 {
987 maxval = val;
988 maxpos = startidx + i;
989 }
990 }
991 }
992 else
993 {
994 for( size_t i = 0; i < total; i++ )
995 {
996 _Tp val = src[i];
997 if( (minval > val || !minpos) && mask[i] )
998 {
999 minval = val;
1000 minpos = startidx + i;
1001 }
1002 if( (maxval < val || !maxpos) && mask[i] )
1003 {
1004 maxval = val;
1005 maxpos = startidx + i;
1006 }
1007 }
1008 }
1009
1010 *_maxval = maxval;
1011 *_minval = minval;
1012 *_maxpos = maxpos;
1013 *_minpos = minpos;
1014}

1017static void setpos( const Mat& mtx, vector<int>& pos, size_t idx )
1018{
1019 pos.resize(mtx.dims);
1020 if( idx > 0 )
1021 {
1022 idx--;
1023 for( int i = mtx.dims-1; i >= 0; i-- )
1024 {
1025 int sz = mtx.size[i]*(i == mtx.dims-1 ? mtx.channels() : 1);
1026 pos[i] = (int)(idx % sz);
1027 idx /= sz;
1028 }
1029 }
1030 else
1031 {
1032 for( int i = mtx.dims-1; i >= 0; i-- )
1033 pos[i] = -1;
1034 }
1035}
1036
1037void minMaxLoc(const Mat& src, double* _minval, double* _maxval,
1038 vector<int>* _minloc, vector<int>* _maxloc,
1039 const Mat& mask)
1040{
1041 CV_Assert( src.channels() == 1 );
1042 const Mat *arrays[]={&src, &mask, 0};
1043 Mat planes[2];
1044
1045 NAryMatIterator it(arrays, planes);
1046 size_t startidx = 1, total = planes[0].total();
1047 size_t i, nplanes = it.nplanes;
1048 int depth = src.depth();
1049 double minval = 0;
1050 double maxval = 0;
1051 size_t maxidx = 0, minidx = 0;
1052
1053 for( i = 0; i < nplanes; i++, ++it, startidx += total )
1054 {
1055 const uchar* sptr = planes[0].data;
1056 const uchar* mptr = planes[1].data;
1057
1058 switch( depth )
1059 {
1060 case CV_8U:
1061 minMaxLoc_((const uchar*)sptr, total, startidx,
1062 &minval, &maxval, &minidx, &maxidx, mptr);
1063 break;
1064 case CV_8S:
1065 minMaxLoc_((const schar*)sptr, total, startidx,
1066 &minval, &maxval, &minidx, &maxidx, mptr);
1067 break;
1068 case CV_16U:
1069 minMaxLoc_((const ushort*)sptr, total, startidx,
1070 &minval, &maxval, &minidx, &maxidx, mptr);
1071 break;
1072 case CV_16S:
1073 minMaxLoc_((const short*)sptr, total, startidx,
1074 &minval, &maxval, &minidx, &maxidx, mptr);
1075 break;
1076 case CV_32S:
1077 minMaxLoc_((const int*)sptr, total, startidx,
1078 &minval, &maxval, &minidx, &maxidx, mptr);
1079 break;
1080 case CV_32F:
1081 minMaxLoc_((const float*)sptr, total, startidx,
1082 &minval, &maxval, &minidx, &maxidx, mptr);
1083 break;
1084 case CV_64F:
1085 minMaxLoc_((const double*)sptr, total, startidx,
1086 &minval, &maxval, &minidx, &maxidx, mptr);
1087 break;
1088 default:
1089 CV_Assert(0);
1090 }
1091 }
1092
1093 if( _maxval )
1094 *_maxval = maxval;
1095 if( _minval )
1096 *_minval = minval;
1097 if( _maxloc )
1098 setpos( src, *_maxloc, maxidx );
1099 if( _minloc )
1100 setpos( src, *_minloc, minidx );
1101}

1103
1104static int
1105normHamming(const uchar* src, size_t total, int cellSize)
1106{
1107 int result = 0;
1108 int mask = cellSize == 1 ? 1 : cellSize == 2 ? 3 : cellSize == 4 ? 15 : -1;
1109 CV_Assert( mask >= 0 );
1110
1111 for( size_t i = 0; i < total; i++ )
1112 {
1113 unsigned a = src[i];
1114 for( ; a != 0; a >>= cellSize )
1115 result += (a & mask) != 0;
1116 }
1117 return result;
1118}

1121template<typename _Tp> static double
1122norm_(const _Tp* src, size_t total, int cn, int normType, double startval, const uchar* mask)
1123{
1124 size_t i;
1125 double result = startval;
1126 if( !mask )
1127 total *= cn;
1128
1129 if( normType == NORM_INF )
1130 {
1131 if( !mask )
1132 for( i = 0; i < total; i++ )
1133 result = std::max(result, (double)std::abs(0+src[i]));// trick with 0 used to quiet gcc warning
1134 else
1135 for( int c = 0; c < cn; c++ )
1136 {
1137 for( i = 0; i < total; i++ )
1138 if( mask[i] )
1139 result = std::max(result, (double)std::abs(0+src[i*cn + c]));
1140 }
1141 }
1142 else if( normType == NORM_L1 )
1143 {
1144 if( !mask )
1145 for( i = 0; i < total; i++ )
1146 result += std::abs(0+src[i]);
1147 else
1148 for( int c = 0; c < cn; c++ )
1149 {
1150 for( i = 0; i < total; i++ )
1151 if( mask[i] )
1152 result += std::abs(0+src[i*cn + c]);
1153 }
1154 }
1155 else
1156 {
1157 if( !mask )
1158 for( i = 0; i < total; i++ )
1159 {
1160 double v = src[i];
1161 result += v*v;
1162 }
1163 else
1164 for( int c = 0; c < cn; c++ )
1165 {
1166 for( i = 0; i < total; i++ )
1167 if( mask[i] )
1168 {
1169 double v = src[i*cn + c];
1170 result += v*v;
1171 }
1172 }
1173 }
1174 return result;
1175}

1178template<typename _Tp> static double
1179norm_(const _Tp* src1, const _Tp* src2, size_t total, int cn, int normType, double startval, const uchar* mask)
1180{
1181 size_t i;
1182 double result = startval;
1183 if( !mask )
1184 total *= cn;
1185
1186 if( normType == NORM_INF )
1187 {
1188 if( !mask )
1189 for( i = 0; i < total; i++ )
1190 result = std::max(result, (double)std::abs(src1[i] - src2[i]));
1191 else
1192 for( int c = 0; c < cn; c++ )
1193 {
1194 for( i = 0; i < total; i++ )
1195 if( mask[i] )
1196 result = std::max(result, (double)std::abs(src1[i*cn + c] - src2[i*cn + c]));
1197 }
1198 }
1199 else if( normType == NORM_L1 )
1200 {
1201 if( !mask )
1202 for( i = 0; i < total; i++ )
1203 result += std::abs(src1[i] - src2[i]);
1204 else
1205 for( int c = 0; c < cn; c++ )
1206 {
1207 for( i = 0; i < total; i++ )
1208 if( mask[i] )
1209 result += std::abs(src1[i*cn + c] - src2[i*cn + c]);
1210 }
1211 }
1212 else
1213 {
1214 if( !mask )
1215 for( i = 0; i < total; i++ )
1216 {
1217 double v = src1[i] - src2[i];
1218 result += v*v;
1219 }
1220 else
1221 for( int c = 0; c < cn; c++ )
1222 {
1223 for( i = 0; i < total; i++ )
1224 if( mask[i] )
1225 {
1226 double v = src1[i*cn + c] - src2[i*cn + c];
1227 result += v*v;
1228 }
1229 }
1230 }
1231 return result;
1232}

1234
1235double norm(const Mat& src, int normType, const Mat& mask)
1236{
1237 if( normType == NORM_HAMMING || normType == NORM_HAMMING2 )
1238 {
1239 if( !mask.empty() )
1240 {
1241 Mat temp;
1242 bitwise_and(src, mask, temp);
1243 return norm(temp, normType, Mat());
1244 }
1245
1246 CV_Assert( src.depth() == CV_8U );
1247
1248 const Mat *arrays[]={&src, 0};
1249 Mat planes[1];
1250
1251 NAryMatIterator it(arrays, planes);
1252 size_t total = planes[0].total();
1253 size_t i, nplanes = it.nplanes;
1254 double result = 0;
1255 int cellSize = normType == NORM_HAMMING ? 1 : 2;
1256
1257 for( i = 0; i < nplanes; i++, ++it )
1258 result += normHamming(planes[0].data, total, cellSize);
1259 return result;
1260 }
1261 int normType0 = normType;
1262 normType = normType == NORM_L2SQR ? NORM_L2 : normType;
1263
1264 CV_Assert( mask.empty() || (src.size == mask.size && mask.type() == CV_8U) );
1265 CV_Assert( normType == NORM_INF || normType == NORM_L1 || normType == NORM_L2 );
1266
1267 const Mat *arrays[]={&src, &mask, 0};
1268 Mat planes[2];
1269
1270 NAryMatIterator it(arrays, planes);
1271 size_t total = planes[0].total();
1272 size_t i, nplanes = it.nplanes;
1273 int depth = src.depth(), cn = planes[0].channels();
1274 double result = 0;
1275
1276 for( i = 0; i < nplanes; i++, ++it )
1277 {
1278 const uchar* sptr = planes[0].data;
1279 const uchar* mptr = planes[1].data;
1280
1281 switch( depth )
1282 {
1283 case CV_8U:
1284 result = norm_((const uchar*)sptr, total, cn, normType, result, mptr);
1285 break;
1286 case CV_8S:
1287 result = norm_((const schar*)sptr, total, cn, normType, result, mptr);
1288 break;
1289 case CV_16U:
1290 result = norm_((const ushort*)sptr, total, cn, normType, result, mptr);
1291 break;
1292 case CV_16S:
1293 result = norm_((const short*)sptr, total, cn, normType, result, mptr);
1294 break;
1295 case CV_32S:
1296 result = norm_((const int*)sptr, total, cn, normType, result, mptr);
1297 break;
1298 case CV_32F:
1299 result = norm_((const float*)sptr, total, cn, normType, result, mptr);
1300 break;
1301 case CV_64F:
1302 result = norm_((const double*)sptr, total, cn, normType, result, mptr);
1303 break;
1304 default:
1305 CV_Error(CV_StsUnsupportedFormat, "");
1306 };
1307 }
1308 if( normType0 == NORM_L2 )
1309 result = sqrt(result);
1310 return result;
1311}

1313
1314double norm(const Mat& src1, const Mat& src2, int normType, const Mat& mask)
1315{
1316 if( normType == NORM_HAMMING || normType == NORM_HAMMING2 )
1317 {
1318 Mat temp;
1319 bitwise_xor(src1, src2, temp);
1320 if( !mask.empty() )
1321 bitwise_and(temp, mask, temp);
1322
1323 CV_Assert( temp.depth() == CV_8U );
1324
1325 const Mat *arrays[]={&temp, 0};
1326 Mat planes[1];
1327
1328 NAryMatIterator it(arrays, planes);
1329 size_t total = planes[0].total();
1330 size_t i, nplanes = it.nplanes;
1331 double result = 0;
1332 int cellSize = normType == NORM_HAMMING ? 1 : 2;
1333
1334 for( i = 0; i < nplanes; i++, ++it )
1335 result += normHamming(planes[0].data, total, cellSize);
1336 return result;
1337 }
1338 int normType0 = normType;
1339 normType = normType == NORM_L2SQR ? NORM_L2 : normType;
1340
1341 CV_Assert( src1.type() == src2.type() && src1.size == src2.size );
1342 CV_Assert( mask.empty() || (src1.size == mask.size && mask.type() == CV_8U) );
1343 CV_Assert( normType == NORM_INF || normType == NORM_L1 || normType == NORM_L2 );
1344 const Mat *arrays[]={&src1, &src2, &mask, 0};
1345 Mat planes[3];
1346
1347 NAryMatIterator it(arrays, planes);
1348 size_t total = planes[0].total();
1349 size_t i, nplanes = it.nplanes;
1350 int depth = src1.depth(), cn = planes[0].channels();
1351 double result = 0;
1352
1353 for( i = 0; i < nplanes; i++, ++it )
1354 {
1355 const uchar* sptr1 = planes[0].data;
1356 const uchar* sptr2 = planes[1].data;
1357 const uchar* mptr = planes[2].data;
1358
1359 switch( depth )
1360 {
1361 case CV_8U:
1362 result = norm_((const uchar*)sptr1, (const uchar*)sptr2, total, cn, normType, result, mptr);
1363 break;
1364 case CV_8S:
1365 result = norm_((const schar*)sptr1, (const schar*)sptr2, total, cn, normType, result, mptr);
1366 break;
1367 case CV_16U:
1368 result = norm_((const ushort*)sptr1, (const ushort*)sptr2, total, cn, normType, result, mptr);
1369 break;
1370 case CV_16S:
1371 result = norm_((const short*)sptr1, (const short*)sptr2, total, cn, normType, result, mptr);
1372 break;
1373 case CV_32S:
1374 result = norm_((const int*)sptr1, (const int*)sptr2, total, cn, normType, result, mptr);
1375 break;
1376 case CV_32F:
1377 result = norm_((const float*)sptr1, (const float*)sptr2, total, cn, normType, result, mptr);
1378 break;
1379 case CV_64F:
1380 result = norm_((const double*)sptr1, (const double*)sptr2, total, cn, normType, result, mptr);
1381 break;
1382 default:
1383 CV_Error(CV_StsUnsupportedFormat, "");
1384 };
1385 }
1386 if( normType0 == NORM_L2 )
1387 result = sqrt(result);
1388 return result;
1389}

1391
1392template<typename _Tp> static double
1393crossCorr_(const _Tp* src1, const _Tp* src2, size_t total)
1394{
1395 double result = 0;
1396 for( size_t i = 0; i < total; i++ )
1397 result += (double)src1[i]*src2[i];
1398 return result;
1399}
1400
1401double crossCorr(const Mat& src1, const Mat& src2)
1402{
1403 CV_Assert( src1.size == src2.size && src1.type() == src2.type() );
1404 const Mat *arrays[]={&src1, &src2, 0};
1405 Mat planes[2];
1406
1407 NAryMatIterator it(arrays, planes);
1408 size_t total = planes[0].total()*planes[0].channels();
1409 size_t i, nplanes = it.nplanes;
1410 int depth = src1.depth();
1411 double result = 0;
1412
1413 for( i = 0; i < nplanes; i++, ++it )
1414 {
1415 const uchar* sptr1 = planes[0].data;
1416 const uchar* sptr2 = planes[1].data;
1417
1418 switch( depth )
1419 {
1420 case CV_8U:
1421 result += crossCorr_((const uchar*)sptr1, (const uchar*)sptr2, total);
1422 break;
1423 case CV_8S:
1424 result += crossCorr_((const schar*)sptr1, (const schar*)sptr2, total);
1425 break;
1426 case CV_16U:
1427 result += crossCorr_((const ushort*)sptr1, (const ushort*)sptr2, total);
1428 break;
1429 case CV_16S:
1430 result += crossCorr_((const short*)sptr1, (const short*)sptr2, total);
1431 break;
1432 case CV_32S:
1433 result += crossCorr_((const int*)sptr1, (const int*)sptr2, total);
1434 break;
1435 case CV_32F:
1436 result += crossCorr_((const float*)sptr1, (const float*)sptr2, total);
1437 break;
1438 case CV_64F:
1439 result += crossCorr_((const double*)sptr1, (const double*)sptr2, total);
1440 break;
1441 default:
1442 CV_Error(CV_StsUnsupportedFormat, "");
1443 };
1444 }
1445 return result;
1446}

1448
1449static void
1450logicOp_(const uchar* src1, const uchar* src2, uchar* dst, size_t total, char c)
1451{
1452 size_t i;
1453 if( c == '&' )
1454 for( i = 0; i < total; i++ )
1455 dst[i] = src1[i] & src2[i];
1456 else if( c == '|' )
1457 for( i = 0; i < total; i++ )
1458 dst[i] = src1[i] | src2[i];
1459 else
1460 for( i = 0; i < total; i++ )
1461 dst[i] = src1[i] ^ src2[i];
1462}
1463
1464static void
1465logicOpS_(const uchar* src, const uchar* scalar, uchar* dst, size_t total, char c)
1466{
1467 const size_t blockSize = 96;
1468 size_t i, j;
1469 if( c == '&' )
1470 for( i = 0; i < total; i += blockSize, dst += blockSize, src += blockSize )
1471 {
1472 size_t sz = MIN(total - i, blockSize);
1473 for( j = 0; j < sz; j++ )
1474 dst[j] = src[j] & scalar[j];
1475 }
1476 else if( c == '|' )
1477 for( i = 0; i < total; i += blockSize, dst += blockSize, src += blockSize )
1478 {
1479 size_t sz = MIN(total - i, blockSize);
1480 for( j = 0; j < sz; j++ )
1481 dst[j] = src[j] | scalar[j];
1482 }
1483 else if( c == '^' )
1484 {
1485 for( i = 0; i < total; i += blockSize, dst += blockSize, src += blockSize )
1486 {
1487 size_t sz = MIN(total - i, blockSize);
1488 for( j = 0; j < sz; j++ )
1489 dst[j] = src[j] ^ scalar[j];
1490 }
1491 }
1492 else
1493 for( i = 0; i < total; i++ )
1494 dst[i] = ~src[i];
1495}

1497
1498void logicOp( const Mat& src1, const Mat& src2, Mat& dst, char op )
1499{
1500 CV_Assert( op == '&' || op == '|' || op == '^' );
1501 CV_Assert( src1.type() == src2.type() && src1.size == src2.size );
1502 dst.create( src1.dims, &src1.size[0], src1.type() );
1503 const Mat *arrays[]={&src1, &src2, &dst, 0};
1504 Mat planes[3];
1505
1506 NAryMatIterator it(arrays, planes);
1507 size_t total = planes[0].total()*planes[0].elemSize();
1508 size_t i, nplanes = it.nplanes;
1509
1510 for( i = 0; i < nplanes; i++, ++it )
1511 {
1512 const uchar* sptr1 = planes[0].data;
1513 const uchar* sptr2 = planes[1].data;
1514 uchar* dptr = planes[2].data;
1515
1516 logicOp_(sptr1, sptr2, dptr, total, op);
1517 }
1518}

1521void logicOp(const Mat& src, const Scalar& s, Mat& dst, char op)
1522{
1523 CV_Assert( op == '&' || op == '|' || op == '^' || op == '~' );
1524 dst.create( src.dims, &src.size[0], src.type() );
1525 const Mat *arrays[]={&src, &dst, 0};
1526 Mat planes[2];
1527
1528 NAryMatIterator it(arrays, planes);
1529 size_t total = planes[0].total()*planes[0].elemSize();
1530 size_t i, nplanes = it.nplanes;
1531 double buf[12];
1532 scalarToRawData(s, buf, src.type(), (int)(96/planes[0].elemSize1()));
1533
1534 for( i = 0; i < nplanes; i++, ++it )
1535 {
1536 const uchar* sptr = planes[0].data;

1540 }

1544template<typename _Tp> static void
1545compare_(const _Tp* src1, const _Tp* src2, uchar* dst, size_t total, int cmpop)
1546{
1547 size_t i;
1548 switch( cmpop )
1549 {
1550 case CMP_LT:
1551 for( i = 0; i < total; i++ )
1552 dst[i] = src1[i] < src2[i] ? 255 : 0;
1553 break;
1554 case CMP_LE:
1555 for( i = 0; i < total; i++ )
1556 dst[i] = src1[i] <= src2[i] ? 255 : 0;
1557 break;
1558 case CMP_EQ:
1559 for( i = 0; i < total; i++ )
1560 dst[i] = src1[i] == src2[i] ? 255 : 0;
1561 break;
1562 case CMP_NE:
1563 for( i = 0; i < total; i++ )
1564 dst[i] = src1[i] != src2[i] ? 255 : 0;
1565 break;
1566 case CMP_GE:
1567 for( i = 0; i < total; i++ )
1568 dst[i] = src1[i] >= src2[i] ? 255 : 0;
1569 break;
1570 case CMP_GT:
1571 for( i = 0; i < total; i++ )
1572 dst[i] = src1[i] > src2[i] ? 255 : 0;
1573 break;
1574 default:
1575 CV_Error(CV_StsBadArg, "Unknown comparison operation");
1576 }
1577}

1711template<typename _Tp> double
1712cmpUlpsInt_(const _Tp* src1, const _Tp* src2, size_t total, int imaxdiff,
1713 size_t startidx, size_t& idx)
1714{
1715 size_t i;
1716 int realmaxdiff = 0;
1717 for( i = 0; i < total; i++ )
1718 {
1719 int diff = std::abs(src1[i] - src2[i]);
1720 if( realmaxdiff < diff )
1721 {
1722 realmaxdiff = diff;
1723 if( diff > imaxdiff && idx == 0 )
1724 idx = i + startidx;
1725 }
1726 }
1727 return realmaxdiff;
1728}

1751static double
1752cmpUlpsFlt_(const int* src1, const int* src2, size_t total, int imaxdiff, size_t startidx, size_t& idx)
1753{

1755 int realmaxdiff = 0;

1758 {

1760 if( a < 0 ) { a ^= C; } if( b < 0 ) { b ^= C; }
1761 int diff = std::abs(a - b);
1762 if( realmaxdiff < diff )
1763 {
1764 realmaxdiff = diff;
1765 if( diff > imaxdiff && idx == 0 )
1766 idx = i + startidx;
1767 }
1768 }
1769 return realmaxdiff;

1794bool cmpUlps(const Mat& src1, const Mat& src2, int imaxDiff, double* _realmaxdiff, vector<int>* loc)
1795{
1796 CV_Assert( src1.type() == src2.type() && src1.size == src2.size );
1797 const Mat *arrays[]={&src1, &src2, 0};
1798 Mat planes[2];
1799 NAryMatIterator it(arrays, planes);
1800 size_t total = planes[0].total()*planes[0].channels();
1801 size_t i, nplanes = it.nplanes;
1802 int depth = src1.depth();
1803 size_t startidx = 1, idx = 0;
1804 if(_realmaxdiff)
1805 *_realmaxdiff = 0;
1806
1807 for( i = 0; i < nplanes; i++, ++it, startidx += total )
1808 {
1809 const uchar* sptr1 = planes[0].data;
1810 const uchar* sptr2 = planes[1].data;
1811 double realmaxdiff = 0;
1812
1813 switch( depth )
1814 {
1815 case CV_8U:
1816 realmaxdiff = cmpUlpsInt_((const uchar*)sptr1, (const uchar*)sptr2, total, imaxDiff, startidx, idx);
1817 break;
1818 case CV_8S:
1819 realmaxdiff = cmpUlpsInt_((const schar*)sptr1, (const schar*)sptr2, total, imaxDiff, startidx, idx);
1820 break;
1821 case CV_16U:
1822 realmaxdiff = cmpUlpsInt_((const ushort*)sptr1, (const ushort*)sptr2, total, imaxDiff, startidx, idx);
1823 break;
1824 case CV_16S:
1825 realmaxdiff = cmpUlpsInt_((const short*)sptr1, (const short*)sptr2, total, imaxDiff, startidx, idx);
1826 break;
1827 case CV_32S:
1828 realmaxdiff = cmpUlpsInt_((const int*)sptr1, (const int*)sptr2, total, imaxDiff, startidx, idx);
1829 break;
1830 case CV_32F:
1831 realmaxdiff = cmpUlpsFlt_((const int*)sptr1, (const int*)sptr2, total, imaxDiff, startidx, idx);
1832 break;
1833 case CV_64F:
1834 realmaxdiff = cmpUlpsFlt_((const int64*)sptr1, (const int64*)sptr2, total, imaxDiff, startidx, idx);
1835 break;
1836 default:
1837 CV_Error(CV_StsUnsupportedFormat, "");
1838 }
1839
1840 if(_realmaxdiff)
1841 *_realmaxdiff = std::max(*_realmaxdiff, realmaxdiff);
1842 }
1843 if(idx > 0 && loc)
1844 setpos(src1, *loc, idx);
1845 return idx == 0;
1846}

1879// checks that the array does not have NaNs and/or Infs and all the elements are
1880// within [min_val,max_val). idx is the index of the first "bad" element.
1881int check( const Mat& a, double fmin, double fmax, vector<int>* _idx )
1882{
1883 const Mat *arrays[]={&a, 0};
1884 Mat plane;
1885 NAryMatIterator it(arrays, &plane);
1886 size_t total = plane.total()*plane.channels();
1887 size_t i, nplanes = it.nplanes;
1888 int depth = a.depth();
1889 size_t startidx = 1, idx = 0;
1890 int imin = 0, imax = 0;
1891
1892 if( depth <= CV_32S )
1893 {
1894 imin = cvCeil(fmin);
1895 imax = cvFloor(fmax);
1896 }
1897
1898 for( i = 0; i < nplanes; i++, ++it, startidx += total )
1899 {
1900 const uchar* aptr = plane.data;
1901
1902 switch( depth )
1903 {
1904 case CV_8U:
1905 checkInt_((const uchar*)aptr, total, imin, imax, startidx, idx);
1906 break;
1907 case CV_8S:
1908 checkInt_((const schar*)aptr, total, imin, imax, startidx, idx);
1909 break;
1910 case CV_16U:
1911 checkInt_((const ushort*)aptr, total, imin, imax, startidx, idx);
1912 break;
1913 case CV_16S:
1914 checkInt_((const short*)aptr, total, imin, imax, startidx, idx);
1915 break;
1916 case CV_32S:
1917 checkInt_((const int*)aptr, total, imin, imax, startidx, idx);
1918 break;
1919 case CV_32F:
1920 checkFlt_((const float*)aptr, total, fmin, fmax, startidx, idx);
1921 break;
1922 case CV_64F:
1923 checkFlt_((const double*)aptr, total, fmin, fmax, startidx, idx);
1924 break;
1925 default:
1926 CV_Error(CV_StsUnsupportedFormat, "");
1927 }
1928
1929 if( idx != 0 )
1930 break;
1931 }
1932
1933 if(idx != 0 && _idx)
1934 setpos(a, *_idx, idx);
1935 return idx == 0 ? 0 : -1;
1936}
1937
1938#define CMP_EPS_OK 0
1939#define CMP_EPS_BIG_DIFF -1
1940#define CMP_EPS_INVALID_TEST_DATA -2 // there is NaN or Inf value in test data
1941#define CMP_EPS_INVALID_REF_DATA -3 // there is NaN or Inf value in reference data
1942
1943// compares two arrays. max_diff is the maximum actual difference,
1944// success_err_level is maximum allowed difference, idx is the index of the first
1945// element for which difference is >success_err_level
1946// (or index of element with the maximum difference)
1947int cmpEps( const Mat& arr, const Mat& refarr, double* _realmaxdiff,
1948 double success_err_level, vector<int>* _idx,
1949 bool element_wise_relative_error )
1950{
1951 CV_Assert( arr.type() == refarr.type() && arr.size == refarr.size );
1952
1953 int ilevel = refarr.depth() <= CV_32S ? cvFloor(success_err_level) : 0;
1954 int result = CMP_EPS_OK;
1955
1956 const Mat *arrays[]={&arr, &refarr, 0};
1957 Mat planes[2];
1958 NAryMatIterator it(arrays, planes);
1959 size_t total = planes[0].total()*planes[0].channels(), j = total;
1960 size_t i, nplanes = it.nplanes;
1961 int depth = arr.depth();
1962 size_t startidx = 1, idx = 0;
1963 double realmaxdiff = 0, maxval = 0;
1964
1965 if(_realmaxdiff)
1966 *_realmaxdiff = 0;
1967
1968 if( refarr.depth() >= CV_32F && !element_wise_relative_error )
1969 {
1970 maxval = cvtest::norm( refarr, NORM_INF );
1971 maxval = MAX(maxval, 1.);
1972 }
1973
1974 for( i = 0; i < nplanes; i++, ++it, startidx += total )
1975 {
1976 const uchar* sptr1 = planes[0].data;
1977 const uchar* sptr2 = planes[1].data;
1978
1979 switch( depth )
1980 {
1981 case CV_8U:
1982 realmaxdiff = cmpUlpsInt_((const uchar*)sptr1, (const uchar*)sptr2, total, ilevel, startidx, idx);
1983 break;
1984 case CV_8S:
1985 realmaxdiff = cmpUlpsInt_((const schar*)sptr1, (const schar*)sptr2, total, ilevel, startidx, idx);
1986 break;
1987 case CV_16U:
1988 realmaxdiff = cmpUlpsInt_((const ushort*)sptr1, (const ushort*)sptr2, total, ilevel, startidx, idx);
1989 break;
1990 case CV_16S:
1991 realmaxdiff = cmpUlpsInt_((const short*)sptr1, (const short*)sptr2, total, ilevel, startidx, idx);
1992 break;
1993 case CV_32S:
1994 realmaxdiff = cmpUlpsInt_((const int*)sptr1, (const int*)sptr2, total, ilevel, startidx, idx);
1995 break;
1996 case CV_32F:
1997 for( j = 0; j < total; j++ )
1998 {
1999 double a_val = ((float*)sptr1)[j];
2000 double b_val = ((float*)sptr2)[j];
2001 double threshold;
2002 if( ((int*)sptr1)[j] == ((int*)sptr2)[j] )
2003 continue;
2004 if( cvIsNaN(a_val) || cvIsInf(a_val) )
2005 {
2006 result = CMP_EPS_INVALID_TEST_DATA;
2007 idx = startidx + j;
2008 break;
2009 }
2010 if( cvIsNaN(b_val) || cvIsInf(b_val) )
2011 {
2012 result = CMP_EPS_INVALID_REF_DATA;
2013 idx = startidx + j;
2014 break;
2015 }
2016 a_val = fabs(a_val - b_val);
2017 threshold = element_wise_relative_error ? fabs(b_val) + 1 : maxval;
2018 if( a_val > threshold*success_err_level )
2019 {
2020 realmaxdiff = a_val/threshold;
2021 if( idx == 0 )
2022 idx = startidx + j;
2023 break;
2024 }
2025 }
2026 break;
2027 case CV_64F:
2028 for( j = 0; j < total; j++ )
2029 {
2030 double a_val = ((double*)sptr1)[j];
2031 double b_val = ((double*)sptr2)[j];
2032 double threshold;
2033 if( ((int64*)sptr1)[j] == ((int64*)sptr2)[j] )
2034 continue;
2035 if( cvIsNaN(a_val) || cvIsInf(a_val) )
2036 {
2037 result = CMP_EPS_INVALID_TEST_DATA;
2038 idx = startidx + j;
2039 break;
2040 }
2041 if( cvIsNaN(b_val) || cvIsInf(b_val) )
2042 {
2043 result = CMP_EPS_INVALID_REF_DATA;
2044 idx = startidx + j;
2045 break;
2046 }
2047 a_val = fabs(a_val - b_val);
2048 threshold = element_wise_relative_error ? fabs(b_val) + 1 : maxval;
2049 if( a_val > threshold*success_err_level )
2050 {
2051 realmaxdiff = a_val/threshold;
2052 idx = startidx + j;
2053 break;
2054 }
2055 }
2056 break;
2057 default:
2058 assert(0);
2059 return CMP_EPS_BIG_DIFF;
2060 }
2061 if(_realmaxdiff)
2062 *_realmaxdiff = MAX(*_realmaxdiff, realmaxdiff);
2063 if( idx != 0 )
2064 break;
2065 }
2066
2067 if( result == 0 && idx != 0 )
2068 result = CMP_EPS_BIG_DIFF;
2069
2070 if( result < -1 && _realmaxdiff )
2071 *_realmaxdiff = exp(1000.);
2072 if(idx > 0 && _idx)
2073 setpos(arr, *_idx, idx);
2074
2075 return result;
2076}

2078
2079int cmpEps2( TS* ts, const Mat& a, const Mat& b, double success_err_level,
2080 bool element_wise_relative_error, const char* desc )
2081{
2082 char msg[100];
2083 double diff = 0;
2084 vector<int> idx;
2085 int code = cmpEps( a, b, &diff, success_err_level, &idx, element_wise_relative_error );
2086
2087 switch( code )
2088 {
2089 case CMP_EPS_BIG_DIFF:
2090 sprintf( msg, "%s: Too big difference (=%g)", desc, diff );
2091 code = TS::FAIL_BAD_ACCURACY;
2092 break;
2093 case CMP_EPS_INVALID_TEST_DATA:
2094 sprintf( msg, "%s: Invalid output", desc );
2095 code = TS::FAIL_INVALID_OUTPUT;
2096 break;
2097 case CMP_EPS_INVALID_REF_DATA:
2098 sprintf( msg, "%s: Invalid reference output", desc );
2099 code = TS::FAIL_INVALID_OUTPUT;
2100 break;
2101 default:
2102 ;
2103 }
2104
2105 if( code < 0 )
2106 {
2107 if( a.total() == 1 )
2108 {
2109 ts->printf( TS::LOG, "%s\n", msg );
2110 }
2111 else if( a.dims == 2 && (a.rows == 1 || a.cols == 1) )
2112 {
2113 ts->printf( TS::LOG, "%s at element %d\n", msg, idx[0] + idx[1] );
2114 }
2115 else
2116 {
2117 string idxstr = vec2str(", ", &idx[0], idx.size());
2118 ts->printf( TS::LOG, "%s at (%s)\n", msg, idxstr.c_str() );
2119 }
2120 }
2121
2122 return code;
2123}

2136template<typename _Tp> static void
2137GEMM_(const _Tp* a_data0, int a_step, int a_delta,
2138 const _Tp* b_data0, int b_step, int b_delta,
2139 const _Tp* c_data0, int c_step, int c_delta,
2140 _Tp* d_data, int d_step,
2141 int d_rows, int d_cols, int a_cols, int cn,
2142 double alpha, double beta)
2143{
2144 for( int i = 0; i < d_rows; i++, d_data += d_step, c_data0 += c_step, a_data0 += a_step )
2145 {
2146 for( int j = 0; j < d_cols; j++ )
2147 {
2148 const _Tp* a_data = a_data0;
2149 const _Tp* b_data = b_data0 + j*b_delta;
2150 const _Tp* c_data = c_data0 + j*c_delta;
2151
2152 if( cn == 1 )
2153 {
2154 double s = 0;
2155 for( int k = 0; k < a_cols; k++ )
2156 {
2157 s += ((double)a_data[0])*b_data[0];
2158 a_data += a_delta;
2159 b_data += b_step;
2160 }
2161 d_data[j] = (_Tp)(s*alpha + (c_data ? c_data[0]*beta : 0));
2162 }
2163 else
2164 {
2165 double s_re = 0, s_im = 0;
2166
2167 for( int k = 0; k < a_cols; k++ )
2168 {
2169 s_re += ((double)a_data[0])*b_data[0] - ((double)a_data[1])*b_data[1];
2170 s_im += ((double)a_data[0])*b_data[1] + ((double)a_data[1])*b_data[0];
2171 a_data += a_delta;
2172 b_data += b_step;
2173 }
2174
2175 s_re *= alpha;
2176 s_im *= alpha;
2177
2178 if( c_data )
2179 {
2180 s_re += c_data[0]*beta;
2181 s_im += c_data[1]*beta;
2182 }
2183
2184 d_data[j*2] = (_Tp)s_re;
2185 d_data[j*2+1] = (_Tp)s_im;
2186 }
2187 }
2188 }
2189}

2191
2192void gemm( const Mat& _a, const Mat& _b, double alpha,
2193 const Mat& _c, double beta, Mat& d, int flags )
2194{
2195 Mat a = _a, b = _b, c = _c;
2196
2197 if( a.data == d.data )
2198 a = a.clone();
2199
2200 if( b.data == d.data )
2201 b = b.clone();
2202
2203 if( !c.empty() && c.data == d.data && (flags & cv::GEMM_3_T) )
2204 c = c.clone();
2205
2206 int a_rows = a.rows, a_cols = a.cols, b_rows = b.rows, b_cols = b.cols;
2207 int cn = a.channels();
2208 int a_step = (int)a.step1(), a_delta = cn;
2209 int b_step = (int)b.step1(), b_delta = cn;
2210 int c_rows = 0, c_cols = 0, c_step = 0, c_delta = 0;
2211
2212 CV_Assert( a.type() == b.type() && a.dims == 2 && b.dims == 2 && cn <= 2 );
2213
2214 if( flags & cv::GEMM_1_T )
2215 {
2216 std::swap( a_rows, a_cols );
2217 std::swap( a_step, a_delta );
2218 }
2219
2220 if( flags & cv::GEMM_2_T )
2221 {
2222 std::swap( b_rows, b_cols );
2223 std::swap( b_step, b_delta );
2224 }
2225
2226 if( !c.empty() )
2227 {
2228 c_rows = c.rows;
2229 c_cols = c.cols;
2230 c_step = (int)c.step1();
2231 c_delta = cn;
2232
2233 if( flags & cv::GEMM_3_T )
2234 {
2235 std::swap( c_rows, c_cols );
2236 std::swap( c_step, c_delta );
2237 }
2238
2239 CV_Assert( c.dims == 2 && c.type() == a.type() && c_rows == a_rows && c_cols == b_cols );
2240 }
2241
2242 d.create(a_rows, b_cols, a.type());
2243
2244 if( a.depth() == CV_32F )
2245 GEMM_(a.ptr<float>(), a_step, a_delta, b.ptr<float>(), b_step, b_delta,
2246 !c.empty() ? c.ptr<float>() : 0, c_step, c_delta, d.ptr<float>(),
2247 (int)d.step1(), a_rows, b_cols, a_cols, cn, alpha, beta );
2248 else
2249 GEMM_(a.ptr<double>(), a_step, a_delta, b.ptr<double>(), b_step, b_delta,
2250 !c.empty() ? c.ptr<double>() : 0, c_step, c_delta, d.ptr<double>(),
2251 (int)d.step1(), a_rows, b_cols, a_cols, cn, alpha, beta );
2252}

2255template<typename _Tp> static void
2256transform_(const _Tp* sptr, _Tp* dptr, size_t total, int scn, int dcn, const double* mat)
2257{
2258 for( size_t i = 0; i < total; i++, sptr += scn, dptr += dcn )
2259 {
2260 for( int j = 0; j < dcn; j++ )
2261 {
2262 double s = mat[j*(scn + 1) + scn];
2263 for( int k = 0; k < scn; k++ )
2264 s += mat[j*(scn + 1) + k]*sptr[k];
2265 dptr[j] = saturate_cast<_Tp>(s);
2266 }
2267 }
2268}

2271void transform( const Mat& src, Mat& dst, const Mat& transmat, const Mat& _shift )
2272{
2273 double mat[20];
2274
2275 int scn = src.channels();
2276 int dcn = dst.channels();
2277 int depth = src.depth();
2278 int mattype = transmat.depth();
2279 Mat shift = _shift.reshape(1, 0);
2280 bool haveShift = !shift.empty();
2281
2282 CV_Assert( scn <= 4 && dcn <= 4 &&
2283 (mattype == CV_32F || mattype == CV_64F) &&
2284 (!haveShift || (shift.type() == mattype && (shift.rows == 1 || shift.cols == 1))) );
2285
2286 // prepare cn x (cn + 1) transform matrix
2287 if( mattype == CV_32F )
2288 {
2289 for( int i = 0; i < transmat.rows; i++ )
2290 {
2291 mat[i*(scn+1)+scn] = 0.;
2292 for( int j = 0; j < transmat.cols; j++ )
2293 mat[i*(scn+1)+j] = transmat.at<float>(i,j);
2294 if( haveShift )
2295 mat[i*(scn+1)+scn] = shift.at<float>(i);
2296 }
2297 }
2298 else
2299 {
2300 for( int i = 0; i < transmat.rows; i++ )
2301 {
2302 mat[i*(scn+1)+scn] = 0.;
2303 for( int j = 0; j < transmat.cols; j++ )
2304 mat[i*(scn+1)+j] = transmat.at<double>(i,j);
2305 if( haveShift )
2306 mat[i*(scn+1)+scn] = shift.at<double>(i);
2307 }
2308 }
2309
2310 const Mat *arrays[]={&src, &dst, 0};
2311 Mat planes[2];
2312 NAryMatIterator it(arrays, planes);
2313 size_t total = planes[0].total();
2314 size_t i, nplanes = it.nplanes;
2315
2316 for( i = 0; i < nplanes; i++, ++it )
2317 {
2318 const uchar* sptr = planes[0].data;
2319 uchar* dptr = planes[1].data;
2320
2321 switch( depth )
2322 {
2323 case CV_8U:
2324 transform_((const uchar*)sptr, (uchar*)dptr, total, scn, dcn, mat);
2325 break;
2326 case CV_8S:
2327 transform_((const schar*)sptr, (schar*)dptr, total, scn, dcn, mat);
2328 break;
2329 case CV_16U:
2330 transform_((const ushort*)sptr, (ushort*)dptr, total, scn, dcn, mat);
2331 break;
2332 case CV_16S:
2333 transform_((const short*)sptr, (short*)dptr, total, scn, dcn, mat);
2334 break;
2335 case CV_32S:
2336 transform_((const int*)sptr, (int*)dptr, total, scn, dcn, mat);
2337 break;
2338 case CV_32F:
2339 transform_((const float*)sptr, (float*)dptr, total, scn, dcn, mat);
2340 break;
2341 case CV_64F:
2342 transform_((const double*)sptr, (double*)dptr, total, scn, dcn, mat);
2343 break;
2344 default:
2345 CV_Error(CV_StsUnsupportedFormat, "");
2346 }
2347 }
2348}

2488muldiv_(const _Tp* src1, const _Tp* src2, _Tp* dst, size_t total, double scale, char op)
2489{
2490 if( op == '*' )
2491 for( size_t i = 0; i < total; i++ )
2492 dst[i] = saturate_cast<_Tp>((scale*src1[i])*src2[i]);
2493 else if( src1 )
2494 for( size_t i = 0; i < total; i++ )
2495 dst[i] = src2[i] ? saturate_cast<_Tp>((scale*src1[i])/src2[i]) : 0;
2496 else
2497 for( size_t i = 0; i < total; i++ )
2498 dst[i] = src2[i] ? saturate_cast<_Tp>(scale/src2[i]) : 0;

2559template<typename _Tp> static void
2560mean_(const _Tp* src, const uchar* mask, size_t total, int cn, Scalar& sum, int& nz)
2561{
2562 if( !mask )
2563 {
2564 nz += (int)total;
2565 total *= cn;
2566 for( size_t i = 0; i < total; i += cn )
2567 {
2568 for( int c = 0; c < cn; c++ )
2569 sum[c] += src[i + c];
2570 }
2571 }
2572 else
2573 {
2574 for( size_t i = 0; i < total; i++ )
2575 if( mask[i] )
2576 {
2577 nz++;
2578 for( int c = 0; c < cn; c++ )
2579 sum[c] += src[i*cn + c];

2619 break;
2620 case CV_32F:
2621 mean_((const float*)sptr, mptr, total, cn, sum, nz);
2622 break;
2623 case CV_64F:
2624 mean_((const double*)sptr, mptr, total, cn, sum, nz);
2625 break;
2626 default:
2627 CV_Error(CV_StsUnsupportedFormat, "");
2628 }
2629 }
2630
2631 return sum * (1./std::max(nz, 1));
2632}

2635void patchZeros( Mat& mat, double level )
2636{
2637 int j, ncols = mat.cols * mat.channels();
2638 int depth = mat.depth();
2639 CV_Assert( depth == CV_32F || depth == CV_64F );
2640
2641 for( int i = 0; i < mat.rows; i++ )
2642 {
2643 if( depth == CV_32F )
2644 {
2645 float* data = mat.ptr<float>(i);
2646 for( j = 0; j < ncols; j++ )
2647 if( fabs(data[j]) < level )
2648 data[j] += 1;
2649 }
2650 else
2651 {
2652 double* data = mat.ptr<double>(i);
2653 for( j = 0; j < ncols; j++ )
2654 if( fabs(data[j]) < level )
2655 data[j] += 1;
2656 }
2657 }
2658}

2660
2661static void calcSobelKernel1D( int order, int _aperture_size, int size, vector<int>& kernel )
2662{
2663 int i, j, oldval, newval;
2664 kernel.resize(size + 1);
2665
2666 if( _aperture_size < 0 )
2667 {
2668 static const int scharr[] = { 3, 10, 3, -1, 0, 1 };
2669 assert( size == 3 );
2670 for( i = 0; i < size; i++ )
2671 kernel[i] = scharr[order*3 + i];
2672 return;
2673 }
2674
2675 for( i = 1; i <= size; i++ )
2676 kernel[i] = 0;
2677 kernel[0] = 1;
2678
2679 for( i = 0; i < size - order - 1; i++ )
2680 {
2681 oldval = kernel[0];
2682 for( j = 1; j <= size; j++ )
2683 {
2684 newval = kernel[j] + kernel[j-1];
2685 kernel[j-1] = oldval;
2686 oldval = newval;
2687 }
2688 }
2689
2690 for( i = 0; i < order; i++ )
2691 {
2692 oldval = -kernel[0];
2693 for( j = 1; j <= size; j++ )
2694 {
2695 newval = kernel[j-1] - kernel[j];
2696 kernel[j-1] = oldval;
2697 oldval = newval;
2698 }
2699 }
2700}
2701
2702
2703Mat calcSobelKernel2D( int dx, int dy, int _aperture_size, int origin )
2704{
2705 CV_Assert( (_aperture_size == -1 || (_aperture_size >= 1 && _aperture_size % 2 == 1)) &&
2706 dx >= 0 && dy >= 0 && dx + dy <= 3 );
2707 Size ksize = _aperture_size == -1 ? Size(3,3) : _aperture_size > 1 ?
2708 Size(_aperture_size, _aperture_size) : dx > 0 ? Size(3, 1) : Size(1, 3);
2709
2710 Mat kernel(ksize, CV_32F);
2711 vector<int> kx, ky;
2712
2713 calcSobelKernel1D( dx, _aperture_size, ksize.width, kx );
2714 calcSobelKernel1D( dy, _aperture_size, ksize.height, ky );
2715
2716 for( int i = 0; i < kernel.rows; i++ )
2717 {
2718 float ay = (float)ky[i]*(origin && (dy & 1) ? -1 : 1);
2719 for( int j = 0; j < kernel.cols; j++ )
2720 kernel.at<float>(i, j) = kx[j]*ay;
2721 }
2722
2723 return kernel;
2724}
2725
2726
2727Mat calcLaplaceKernel2D( int aperture_size )
2728{
2729 int ksize = aperture_size == 1 ? 3 : aperture_size;
2730 Mat kernel(ksize, ksize, CV_32F);
2731
2732 vector<int> kx, ky;
2733
2734 calcSobelKernel1D( 2, aperture_size, ksize, kx );
2735 if( aperture_size > 1 )
2736 calcSobelKernel1D( 0, aperture_size, ksize, ky );
2737 else
2738 {
2739 ky.resize(3);
2740 ky[0] = ky[2] = 0; ky[1] = 1;
2741 }
2742
2743 for( int i = 0; i < ksize; i++ )
2744 for( int j = 0; j < ksize; j++ )
2745 kernel.at<float>(i, j) = (float)(kx[j]*ky[i] + kx[i]*ky[j]);
2746
2747 return kernel;
2748}

2750
2751void initUndistortMap( const Mat& _a0, const Mat& _k0, Size sz, Mat& _mapx, Mat& _mapy )
2752{
2753 _mapx.create(sz, CV_32F);
2754 _mapy.create(sz, CV_32F);
2755
2756 double a[9], k[5]={0,0,0,0,0};
2757 Mat _a(3, 3, CV_64F, a);
2758 Mat _k(_k0.rows,_k0.cols, CV_MAKETYPE(CV_64F,_k0.channels()),k);
2759 double fx, fy, cx, cy, ifx, ify, cxn, cyn;
2760
2761 _a0.convertTo(_a, CV_64F);
2762 _k0.convertTo(_k, CV_64F);
2763 fx = a[0]; fy = a[4]; cx = a[2]; cy = a[5];
2764 ifx = 1./fx; ify = 1./fy;
2765 cxn = cx;
2766 cyn = cy;
2767
2768 for( int v = 0; v < sz.height; v++ )
2769 {
2770 for( int u = 0; u < sz.width; u++ )
2771 {
2772 double x = (u - cxn)*ifx;
2773 double y = (v - cyn)*ify;
2774 double x2 = x*x, y2 = y*y;
2775 double r2 = x2 + y2;
2776 double cdist = 1 + (k[0] + (k[1] + k[4]*r2)*r2)*r2;
2777 double x1 = x*cdist + k[2]*2*x*y + k[3]*(r2 + 2*x2);
2778 double y1 = y*cdist + k[3]*2*x*y + k[2]*(r2 + 2*y2);
2779
2780 _mapy.at<float>(v, u) = (float)(y1*fy + cy);
2781 _mapx.at<float>(v, u) = (float)(x1*fx + cx);
2782 }
2783 }
2784}

2801
2802static Mat getSubArray(const Mat& m, int border, vector<int>& ofs0, vector<int>& ofs)
2803{
2804 ofs.resize(ofs0.size());
2805 if( border < 0 )
2806 {
2807 std::copy(ofs0.begin(), ofs0.end(), ofs.begin());
2808 return m;
2809 }
2810 int i, d = m.dims;
2811 CV_Assert(d == (int)ofs.size());
2812 vector<Range> r(d);
2813 for( i = 0; i < d; i++ )
2814 {
2815 r[i].start = std::max(0, ofs0[i] - border);
2816 r[i].end = std::min(ofs0[i] + 1 + border, m.size[i]);
2817 ofs[i] = std::min(ofs0[i], border);
2818 }
2819 return m(&r[0]);
2820}

2822template<typename _Tp, typename _WTp> static void
2823writeElems(std::ostream& out, const void* data, int nelems, int starpos)
2824{
2825 for(int i = 0; i < nelems; i++)
2826 {
2827 if( i == starpos )
2828 out << "*";
2829 out << (_WTp)((_Tp*)data)[i];
2830 if( i == starpos )
2831 out << "*";
2832 out << (i+1 < nelems ? ", " : "");
2833 }
2834}

2836
2837static void writeElems(std::ostream& out, const void* data, int nelems, int depth, int starpos)
2838{
2839 if(depth == CV_8U)
2840 writeElems<uchar, int>(out, data, nelems, starpos);
2841 else if(depth == CV_8S)
2842 writeElems<schar, int>(out, data, nelems, starpos);
2843 else if(depth == CV_16U)
2844 writeElems<ushort, int>(out, data, nelems, starpos);
2845 else if(depth == CV_16S)
2846 writeElems<short, int>(out, data, nelems, starpos);
2847 else if(depth == CV_32S)
2848 writeElems<int, int>(out, data, nelems, starpos);
2849 else if(depth == CV_32F)
2850 {
2851 std::streamsize pp = out.precision();
2852 out.precision(8);
2853 writeElems<float, float>(out, data, nelems, starpos);
2854 out.precision(pp);
2855 }
2856 else if(depth == CV_64F)
2857 {
2858 std::streamsize pp = out.precision();
2859 out.precision(16);
2860 writeElems<double, double>(out, data, nelems, starpos);
2861 out.precision(pp);
2862 }
2863 else
2864 CV_Error(CV_StsUnsupportedFormat, "");
2865}

2868struct MatPart
2869{
2870 MatPart(const Mat& _m, const vector<int>* _loc)
2871 : m(&_m), loc(_loc) {}
2872 const Mat* m;
2873 const vector<int>* loc;
2874};
2875
2876static std::ostream& operator << (std::ostream& out, const MatPart& m)
2877{
2878 CV_Assert( !m.loc || ((int)m.loc->size() == m.m->dims && m.m->dims <= 2) );
2879 if( !m.loc )
2880 out << *m.m;
2881 else
2882 {
2883 int i, depth = m.m->depth(), cn = m.m->channels(), width = m.m->cols*cn;
2884 for( i = 0; i < m.m->rows; i++ )
2885 {
2886 writeElems(out, m.m->ptr(i), width, depth, i == (*m.loc)[0] ? (*m.loc)[1] : -1);
2887 out << (i < m.m->rows-1 ? ";\n" : "");
2888 }
2889 }
2890 return out;
2891}

2893MatComparator::MatComparator(double _maxdiff, int _context)
2894 : maxdiff(_maxdiff), context(_context) {}
2895
2896::testing::AssertionResult
2897MatComparator::operator()(const char* expr1, const char* expr2,
2898 const Mat& m1, const Mat& m2)
2899{
2900 if( m1.type() != m2.type() || m1.size != m2.size )
2901 return ::testing::AssertionFailure()
2902 << "The reference and the actual output arrays have different type or size:\n"
2903 << expr1 << " ~ " << MatInfo(m1) << "\n"
2904 << expr2 << " ~ " << MatInfo(m2) << "\n";
2905
2906 //bool ok = cvtest::cmpUlps(m1, m2, maxdiff, &realmaxdiff, &loc0);
2907 int code = cmpEps( m1, m2, &realmaxdiff, maxdiff, &loc0, true);
2908
2909 if(code >= 0)
2910 return ::testing::AssertionSuccess();
2911
2912 Mat m[] = {m1.reshape(1,0), m2.reshape(1,0)};
2913 int dims = m[0].dims;
2914 vector<int> loc;
2915 int border = dims <= 2 ? context : 0;
2916
2917 Mat m1part, m2part;
2918 if( border == 0 )
2919 {
2920 loc = loc0;
2921 m1part = Mat(1, 1, m[0].depth(), m[0].ptr(&loc[0]));
2922 m2part = Mat(1, 1, m[1].depth(), m[1].ptr(&loc[0]));
2923 }
2924 else
2925 {
2926 m1part = getSubArray(m[0], border, loc0, loc);
2927 m2part = getSubArray(m[1], border, loc0, loc);
2928 }
2929
2930 return ::testing::AssertionFailure()
2931 << "too big relative difference (" << realmaxdiff << " > "
2932 << maxdiff << ") between "
2933 << MatInfo(m1) << " '" << expr1 << "' and '" << expr2 << "' at " << Mat(loc0) << ".\n\n"
2934 << "'" << expr1 << "': " << MatPart(m1part, border > 0 ? &loc : 0) << ".\n\n"
2935 << "'" << expr2 << "': " << MatPart(m2part, border > 0 ? &loc : 0) << ".\n";
2936}
